'''Jefferson Starship''' is a rock band formed in the 1970s. The group performed the song "[[Light the Sky on Fire]]" as an [[Unidentified Human band|unnamed band]] for a musical sequence in ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''. The members involved in the special were [[Unidentified Human singer (Blockade of Kashyyyk)|lead singer]] [[Marty Balin]], [[Unidentified Human drummer (Blockade of Kashyyyk)|drummer]] [[John Barbata]], lead guitarist [[Craig Chaquico]], [[Unidentified Human keyboardist (Blockade of Kashyyyk)|keyboardist]] [[David Freiberg]], rhythm guitarist [[Paul Kantner]], bass clarinetist [[Steven Schuster]], and bassist [[Pete Sears]].

==History==
In the early 1970s, [[Tom Veitch]], who would later write ''Star Wars'' comics, wrote two issues of a comic book for Jefferson Starship's vanity label [[Wikipedia:Grunt Records|Grunt Records]].<ref name="Veitch">{{WebCite|url=http://www.dcinthe80s.com/2016/08/the-tom-veitch-interview-part-one.html|text=The Tom Veitch interview -- part one|date=2018-11-13|archivedate=20240427162617}}</ref>

In June of [[1977]], the group was photographed with [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] (as played by touring model [[Kermit Eller]]).<ref>{{Getty|subdomain=www|lang=ae|url=detail/news-photo/star-wars-villain-darth-vader-meets-jefferson-starship-news-photo/635236841|text=Grace Slick and Darth Vader|author=Ressmeyer, Roger|date=1977-06-24}}</ref> Sometime later, Grace Slick met [[Mark Hamill]] backstage at a concert, where she introduced herself as "Darth Vader's wife."<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://people.com/archive/cover-story-mark-hamill-strikes-back-vol-16-no-9|text=Mark Hamill Strikes Back|author=Lague, Louise|date=1981-08-31|work=[[Wikipedia:People (magazine)|''People'']]|archivedate=20191022020142}}</ref> By [[1978]], Creach and Slick had departed from the group. It was during this period that the group performed in ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''. Balin and Barbata soon departed the group as well.

